---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="What Is L. reuteri Yoghurt? Strains & Gut Health | Yoghurt of Youth"
  description="Discover live L. reuteri probiotic yoghurt — the DSM 17648, DSM 17938 and ATCC PTA 6475 strains we ferment, how live cultures support gut health, and how to enjoy it."
>
  <section
    id="about"
    class="relative scroll-mt-32 md:scroll-mt-24 text-white py-12"
    style="background-image: linear-gradient(rgba(0,0,0,0.65), rgba(0,0,0,0.65)), url('/about_bg.webp'); background-size: cover; background-position: 50% center; background-repeat: no-repeat;"
  >
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-8">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold text-white">
        L. reuteri Probiotic Yoghurt &amp; Gut Health
      </h1>

      <p class="mt-4 text-white">
        Each of our yoghurts is efficiently fermented with live
        <em>Lactobacillus reuteri</em> strains that have been studied for
        their unique, health-supporting properties.
      </p>

      <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">PRCXN — DSM 17648</h4>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
            DSM&nbsp;17648 is a strain that researchers have studied for its
            interaction with <em>Helicobacter pylori</em>, a common stomach
            bacterium. In laboratory studies, this strain has been observed to
            bind to <em>H. pylori</em> cells. It is one of the most-researched
            <em>L. reuteri</em> strains in this area.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">SPCTRL — DSM 17938</h4>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
            A broad-acting <em>L. reuteri</em> strain observed in studies to
            help limit unwanted microbes, including <em>Candida</em> species,
            while coexisting peacefully with beneficial flora. It contributes
            to microbial balance throughout the gut and is widely recognised
            for its excellent safety record.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div>
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-white">LVLV — ATCC PTA 6475</h4>
          <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
            ATCC&nbsp;PTA&nbsp;6475 is an <em>L. reuteri</em> strain studied for
            its antipathogenic activity and, in research settings, for its
            relationship with the gut–brain axis, including pathways involving
            oxytocin stimulation. It is one of the more extensively researched
            <em>L. reuteri</em> strains in connection with these systemic
            effects.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
        Why Gut Health Matters
      </h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Modern research consistently links gut balance to nearly every aspect
        of wellbeing. Scientific studies suggest that a well-functioning
        microbiome influences:
      </p>

      <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white leading-relaxed">
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li><strong>General wellbeing &amp; energy</strong> – balanced digestion and reduced bloating promote comfort and nutrient absorption.</li>
          <li><strong>Indigestion</strong> – dysbiosis and intestinal inflammation are central to gut issues; balanced flora can help stabilise the gut environment.</li>
          <li><strong>Nutrient deficiencies</strong> – microbial imbalances can impair absorption of iron, B-vitamins, and magnesium.</li>
          <li><strong>Chronic inflammation &amp; disease</strong> – microbial metabolites regulate immune signalling throughout the body.</li>
          <li><strong>Cardiovascular health</strong> – balanced gut flora correlates with healthy blood pressure and cholesterol.</li>
          <li><strong>Kidney health &amp; joint health</strong> – certain microbes degrade oxalate and uric acid, helping the body excrete them safely.</li>
          <li><strong>Bile sludge &amp; fat digestion</strong> – microbial enzymes aid bile circulation and emulsify fats efficiently.</li>
          <li><strong>Obesity &amp; blood sugar</strong> – gut composition affects insulin sensitivity and energy storage.</li>
          <li><strong>Mental health &amp; cognition</strong> – the gut–brain axis influences mood, clarity, and focus. Studies link dysbiosis with depression, anxiety, and brain fog.</li>
          <li><strong>Stress &amp; sleep</strong> – gut microbes help regulate serotonin and melatonin production.</li>
          <li><strong>Ageing &amp; inflammaging</strong> – balanced microbiota reduce chronic low-grade inflammation, the driver of premature ageing.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Restoring microbial balance can therefore ripple through every system
        of the body.
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-white">
        The Power of <em>Lactobacillus reuteri</em>
      </h3>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Our three <em>L. reuteri</em> strains have each been researched for
        complementary roles in the gut:
      </p>

      <ul class="mt-2 list-disc list-inside text-sm text-white space-y-1">
        <li>
          <strong>DSM&nbsp;17648 (“PRCXN”)</strong> has been studied for its ability to
          bind to <em>Helicobacter pylori</em> in the stomach, by forming complexes that
          are naturally cleared through digestion.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>DSM&nbsp;17938 (“SPCTRL”)</strong> promotes a balanced gut environment by
          limiting the overgrowth of opportunistic species, including <em>Candida</em>,
          while reinforcing a healthy microbial community along the intestinal tract.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>ATCC&nbsp;PTA&nbsp;6475 (“LVLV”)</strong> has been studied for its
          antipathogenic activity and for its role in the gut–brain axis, pertaining
          to oxytocin stimulation and systemic wellbeing.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Used together in rotation,
        <strong>PRCXN, SPCTRL and LVLV have each been studied for complementary roles</strong>:
        one researched in connection with <em>H.&nbsp;pylori</em>, one for supporting general
        microbial balance downstream in the gut, and one for its stimulation of oxytocin in
        the gut. This layered approach can greatly support systemic health.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        When the three yoghurts are taken in rotation, they help create a more resilient digestive ecosystem
        less prone to inflammation, laying a foundation for lasting digestive harmony and whole-body wellbeing.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        Each bottle of yoghurt contains 250&nbsp;ml,
        delivering live counts on the order of <strong>one trillion CFU</strong>, a level consistent
        with genuine biological effect.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        All of our yoghurts are lactose-free to minimise negative reactions.
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Scientific Studies</h3>
      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm">
        Independent research exploring the strains we use:
      </p>

      <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-2 space-y-1 text-sm text-white">
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Holz et&nbsp;al., 2015 (Beneficial Microbes):</span>
          &nbsp;<em>L. reuteri</em> DSM&nbsp;17648 reduced <em>H. pylori</em> colonisation in humans.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Indrio et&nbsp;al., 2014 (Journal of Pediatrics):</span>
          &nbsp;DSM&nbsp;17938 supported gastrointestinal function in infants; widely studied for tolerance and safety.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Savino et&nbsp;al., 2020 (BMC Gastroenterology):</span>
          &nbsp;Reviews on <em>L. reuteri</em> and microbial balance.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Su et&nbsp;al., 2023 (Frontiers in Microbiology):</span>
          &nbsp;Review describing how combining probiotic strains with complementary mechanisms
          enhances suppression of <em>H.&nbsp;pylori</em> and supports restoration of healthy microbiota.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Poutahidis et&nbsp;al., 2013 (PLOS ONE):</span>
          &nbsp;<em>L. reuteri</em> ATCC&nbsp;PTA&nbsp;6475 was observed to up-regulate oxytocin and accelerate wound healing in mice, a finding researchers have linked to gut–brain signalling.
        </li>
        <li>
          <span class="font-medium">Li et&nbsp;al., 2022 (npj Biofilms and Microbiomes):</span>
          &nbsp;A one-year randomised human trial found <em>L. reuteri</em> ATCC&nbsp;PTA&nbsp;6475 supplementation supported gut microbiota richness and inflammatory status in older women.
        </li>
      </ol>

      <p class="mt-3 text-white text-xs leading-relaxed">
        Disclaimer: This information summarises findings from independent scientific
        research on the bacterial strains used. It is provided for educational
        purposes and is not medical advice. Original publications available via
        PubMed and other open scientific databases. Our products are fermented foods
        intended to support natural gut balance as part of a healthy lifestyle.
      </p>

      <h3 class="mt-8 text-xl font-semibold text-white">Instructions</h3>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">
        The yoghurt may be consumed at any time in the day, but for best effect, it is recommended to have it 
        on an empty stomach. This allows the beneficial bacteria to reach the gut unimpeded.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-2 text-white text-sm leading-relaxed">Please do the following:</p>

      <div class="mt-2 text-sm text-white leading-relaxed">
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-1">
          <li>Natural yoghurt can separate, which is perfectly natural, so shake well before use.</li>
          <li>Keep refrigerated.</li>
          <li>Consume within 3 days of opening.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

